#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.158"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.158:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.158:0.2"
msgid "16. Indriyavagga"
msgstr "16. Faculties"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: parihāṇisuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.158:0.3"
msgid "158. Parihānisutta"
msgstr "158. Decline"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.144"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.158:1.1"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an4.158:1.2"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an4.158:1.3"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "an4.158:1.4"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr "Sāriputta said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.158:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Yo hi koci, āvuso, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā cattāro dhamme attani "
"samanupassati, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, any monk or nun who sees four things inside themselves should "
"conclude:"

msgctxt "an4.158:2.2"
msgid "‘parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’."
msgstr "‘My skillful qualities are declining."

msgctxt "an4.158:2.3"
msgid "Parihānametaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā."
msgstr "For this is what the Buddha calls decline.’"

msgctxt "an4.158:2.4"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

# See BB’s note on the readings of thanathanesu. Here I adopt the PTS reading. Cf. other contexts where pannacakkhu is used, eg SN 41.7: “te gambhīre buddhavacane paññācakkhu kamatī”.
#. VAR: Rāgavepullattaṃ → rāgavepullataṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.158:2.5"
msgid ""
"Rāgavepullattaṃ, dosavepullattaṃ, mohavepullattaṃ, gambhīresu kho panassa "
"ṭhānāṭhānesu paññācakkhu na kamati."
msgstr ""
"They have much greed, much hate, and much delusion; and their wisdom eye "
"doesn’t go into the many deep matters."

msgctxt "an4.158:2.6"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, āvuso, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā ime cattāro dhamme attani "
"samanupassati, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Any monk or nun who sees these four things inside themselves should conclude:"

msgctxt "an4.158:2.7"
msgid "‘parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’."
msgstr "‘My skillful qualities are declining."

msgctxt "an4.158:2.8"
msgid "Parihānametaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā."
msgstr "For this is what the Buddha calls decline.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.158:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, āvuso, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā cattāro dhamme attani "
"samanupassati, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr "Any monk or nun who sees four things inside themselves should conclude:"

msgctxt "an4.158:3.2"
msgid "‘na parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’."
msgstr "‘My skillful qualities are not declining."

msgctxt "an4.158:3.3"
msgid "Aparihānametaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā."
msgstr "For this is what the Buddha calls non-decline.’"

msgctxt "an4.158:3.4"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

#. VAR: Rāgatanuttaṃ → rāgatanuttanaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an4.158:3.5"
msgid ""
"Rāgatanuttaṃ, dosatanuttaṃ, mohatanuttaṃ, gambhīresu kho panassa "
"ṭhānāṭhānesu paññācakkhu kamati."
msgstr ""
"Their greed, hate, and delusion grow less; and their wisdom eye goes into "
"the many deep matters."

msgctxt "an4.158:3.6"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, āvuso, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā ime cattāro dhamme attani "
"samanupassati, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Any monk or nun who sees these four things inside themselves should conclude:"

msgctxt "an4.158:3.7"
msgid "‘na parihāyāmi kusalehi dhammehi’."
msgstr "‘My skillful qualities are not declining."

msgctxt "an4.158:3.8"
msgid "Aparihānametaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr "For this is what the Buddha calls non-decline.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.158:3.9"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
